commit.message: Add Python 3.8 classifier to setup.py

Add support for Django 3.0

#721

Following django/django@4122d9d3f1983eea612f236e941d937bd8589a0d, this changes the model `save()` logic to get `self.parent` before (rather than after) setting `self.parent_id` (when it is setting `self.parent_id` to the old parent ID).

I'm not particularly confident of the fix, since I'm not sure how it was guaranteed that `self.parent` and `self.parent_id` are consistent prior to django/django@4122d9d3f1983eea612f236e941d937bd8589a0d.

Nonetheless, this gets tests passing, so if there are problems with this approach I think additional tests should be added.

Add Python 3.8 to test matrix

Note that only Django 2.2.8 and newer officially support Python 3.8: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/faq/install/#what-python-version-can-i-use-with-django
Removing deprecated functions for Django 3
Import FieldDoesNotExist from django.core.exceptions

commit.message:
Error messages should use the error level

When displaying errors in the admin message_user, we should use
messages.ERROR as the level so the message will look like an error.
Without this, all errors show up green with a checkmark.
